In JIRA 4.4 a user could press the down arrow and scroll through the list of assignable users. In JIRA 5.0.1 this is no longer possible: only the "suggested users" are shown unless you type at least 1 character:

!assignee suggestion.png!

The "suggested users" list is populated from the issue's history and the user's history, so in some cases it won't contain much at all apart from "Automatic" and "Unassigned". I think the usability could be improved here.

{panel:title=Workaround| borderStyle=dashed| borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#F7D6C1| bgColor=#FFFFCE} 

If this is an issue you should be able to directly input the user name and it should save (the autocomplete simply has stopped working). 
But a full work around could be to disable the new assignee picker and revert to the old dropdown. To do this, restart with -Datlassian.darkfeature.frother.assignee.field=false. See [Setting Properties and Options on Startup|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Setting+Properties+and+Options+on+Startup].

A *full* guide on how to do this has been written here: [How to fully render assignee drop down list|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/How+to+fully+render+assignee+drop-down+list].

This has also been fixed in JIRA 5.1.1 bugfix release so an upgrade will also resolve the issue.
{panel}

